<item>
            <title>[OAK-7982] ACL.addEntry: check for mandatory restrictions only respects single value restrictions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-7982</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The validation of &lt;tt&gt;ACL.addEntry(Principal principal, Privilege[] privileges, boolean isAllow, Map&amp;lt;String, Value&amp;gt; restrictions, Map&amp;lt;String, Value[]&amp;gt; mvRestrictions)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
includes a check that mandatory restrictions are actually present.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the code performing that check only tests if the mandatory restrictions are included in the &lt;tt&gt;restrictions&lt;/tt&gt; ignoring the fact that a mandatory restriction might be multi-valued and thus provided in the &lt;tt&gt;mvRestrictions&lt;/tt&gt; param.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stillalex&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stillalex&quot;&gt;stillalex&lt;/a&gt; fyi.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
